Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1198
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 35-31.5-2; IC 35-43-2.5.
Synopsis: Use of public restrooms. Makes it a Class B misdemeanor
if: (1) a male knowingly or intentionally enters a restroom that is
designated to be used only by females; or (2) a female knowingly or
intentionally enters a restroom that is designated to be used only by
males. Provides certain defenses.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Borders
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Courts and Criminal Code.
